obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (8352)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for sub-sections (1) and (2) (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8352&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) This Act may be called the Metro Railways`
  line `(Operation and Maintenance) Act, 2002.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends in the first instance to the National Capital Region and the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, after consultation with the State Government, extend this Act to such other metropolitan area`
  line `and metropolitan city, except the metropolitan city of Calcutta, and with effect from such date as may be`
  line `specified in that notification and thereupon the provisions of this Act shall apply to that metropolitan area`
  line `or metropolitan city accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 29th day of October, 2002.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (8353)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8353&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) "Central Government", in relation to technical planning and safety of metro railways, means`
  line `the Ministry of the Government of India dealing with Railways;`
  line
  line `(aa) "Claims Commissioner" means a Claims Commissioner appointed under section 48;]`
  line
  line `(b) "Commissioner" means the Commissioner of the Metro Railway Safety appointed under`
  line `section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) "development" with its grammatical variations means the carrying out of building,`
  line `engineering, mining or other operations in, on, over or under land or the making of any material`
  line `change on any building, or land, or planting of any tree on land and includes redevelopment;`
  line
  line `(d) "electric supply-line" shall have the meaning assigned to it under clause (f) of section 2 of the`
  line `Indian Electricity Act, 1910 (9 of 1910);`
  line
  line `(e) "fare" means the charge levied for the carriage of passengers;`
  line
  line `(f) "Government metro railway" means a metro railway owned by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(g) "land" includes any right or interest in any land;`
  line
  line `^2[(h) "metropolitan area" shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (c) of article 243P of the`
  line Constitution;
  line
  line `(ha) "metropolitan city" means the metropolitan city of Bombay, Calcutta, Delhi or Madras;]`
  line
  line `(i) "metro railway" means rail-guided mass rapid transit system having dedicated right-of-way,`
  line `with steel wheel or rubber-tyred wheel coaches, but excluding tramways, for carriage of passengers,`
  line `and includes--`
  line
  line `(A) all land within the boundary marks indicating the limits of the land appurtenant to a metro`
  line railway,
  line
  line `(B) all rails tracks, sidings, yards or branches worked over for the purposes of, or in`
  line `connection with, a metro railway,`
  line
  line `(C) all stations, offices, ventilation shafts and ducts, warehouses, workshops, manufactories,`
  line `fixed plants and machineries, sheds, depots and other works constructed for the purpose of, or in`
  line `connection with, a metro railway;`
  line
  line `(j) "metro railway administration" in relation to--`
  line
  line `(i) a Government metro railway means the General Manager of that railway; or`
  line
  line `(ii) an on-Government metro railway means the person who is the owner or lessee of that`
  line `metro railway or the person working that metro railway under an arrangement with the owner`
  line `or lessee of that metro railway;`
  line
  line `(k) "metro railway official" means any person employed by the Central Government or by a`
  line `metro railway administration in connection with the services of a metro railway;`
  line
  line `^3[(ka) "National Capital Region" means the National Capital Region as defined in clause (f) of`
  line `section 2 of the National Capital Region Planning Board Act, 1985 (2 of 1985);]`
  line
  line `(l) "non-Government metro railway" means a metro railway other than a Government metro`
  line railway;
  line
  line `(m) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(n) "pass" means an authority given by the metro railway administration or by an officer`
  line `appointed by that administration in this behalf, to a person allowing him to travel as a passenger on`
  line `the metro railway, but does not include a ticket;`
  line
  line `(o) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made by the Central Government under this Act;`
  line
  line `(p) "railway" shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (31) of section 2 of the Railways`
  line `Act, 1989 (24 of 1989);`
  line
  line `(q) "regulations" means the regulations made by the Government metro railway administration`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(r) "rolling stock" includes locomotives, engines, carriages (whether powered or not), wagons,`
  line `trollies and vehicles of all kinds moving or intended to move on rails; and`
  line
  line `(s) "telegraph line" shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (4) of section 3 of the Indian`
  line `Telegraph Act, 1885 (13 of 1885).`
  line
  line `(2) All other words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Metro Railways`
  line `(Construction of Works) Act, 1978 (33 of 1978) shall have the meanings, respectively, assigned to them`
  line `in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for clause (a) (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for clause (h) (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 34 of 2009, s. 7 (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (8354)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of Government metro railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "metropolitan city of Delhi" (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8354&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, for the purpose`
  line `of efficient administration of a Government metro railway, in ^1[the National Capital Region, metropolitan`
  line `city and metropolitan area], by notification, constitute such railways as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) A Government metro railway administration may, for efficient performance of its functions under`
  line `this Act, appoint such officers and other employees as it considers necessary on such terms and conditions`
  line `of service as may be determined by regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (8355)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Appointment of General Manager.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8355&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification, appoint`
  line `a person to be the General Manager of a Government metro railway.`
  line
  line `(2) The general superintendence and control of a Government metro railway shall vest in the General`
  line Manager.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (8356)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Functions of metro railway administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1 . Subs. by Act 34 of 2009, s. 5 for "metropolitan city of Delhi" (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8356&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The functions of a metro railway administration`
  line `shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) to maintain and operate metro railway, for public carriage of passengers, constructed in, upon, across, under or over any land, building, street, road or passage in ^1[the National Capital Region, metropolitan city and metropolitan area]; and`
  line
  line `(b) to engage in any such other activities or perform such other functions as may be considered`
  line `necessary for the purpose of the operation and maintenance of the metro railway in ^1[the National Capital Region, metropolitan city and metropolitan area].`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (8357)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Powers of metro railway administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8357&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The metro railway administration shall have the`
  line `power to do anything which may be necessary or expedient for the purpose of carrying out its functions`
  line `under the Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provision, such power shall include the power`
  line to--
  line
  line `(a) acquire, hold and dispose of all kinds of properties owned by it, both movable and`
  line immovable;
  line
  line `(b) improve, develop or alter any property or asset held by it;`
  line
  line `^1[(ba) develop any metro railway land for commercial use;`
  line
  line `(bb) provide for carriage of passengers by integrated transport services or any other mode of`
  line transport;]
  line
  line `(c) center temporarily in or upon the lands adjoining the metro railway alignment in order to`
  line `remove obstruction, or prevent imminent danger from any source, such as tree, post or structure,`
  line `which may obstruct the movement of the rolling stock, or passengers, or the view of the signal`
  line `provided for movement of the rolling stock;`
  line
  line `(d) execute any lease or grant any licence in respect of the property held by it;`
  line
  line `(e) enter into, assign and rescind any contract or obligation;`
  line
  line `(f) employ an agent or contractor for discharging its functions;`
  line
  line `(g) obtain licence from the Central Government to establish and maintain telegraph lines;`
  line
  line `(h) lay down or place electric supply lines for conveyance and transmission of energy and to`
  line `obtain licence for that purpose; and`
  line
  line `(i) do all incidental acts as are necessary for discharge of any function conferred, or imposed, on`
  line `it by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (8358)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Appointment of Commissioner of Metro Railway Safety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8358&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The Central Government may`
  line `appoint one or more Commissioners of Metro Railway Safety.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The Commissioner shall function under the administrative control of the Chief Commissioner of`
  line `Railway Safety appointed under section 5 of the Railways Act, 1989 (24 of 1989).]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. S. 7 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w. e. f. 7-9-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (8359)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Duties of Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8359&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner shall--`
  line
  line `(a) inspect the metro railway with a view to determine whether it is fit to be opened for the`
  line `public carriage of passengers and report thereon to the Central Government as required by or under`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) make such periodical or other inspections of metro railway, its rolling stock used thereon`
  line `and its other installations as the Central Government may direct;`
  line
  line `(c) make an inquiry under the provisions of this Act into the cause of any accident on the metro`
  line `railway; and`
  line
  line `(d) discharge such other duties as are conferred on him by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (8360)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Powers of Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8360&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the control of the Central Government, the Commissioner,`
  line `whenever it is necessary so to do for any of the purposes of this Act, may--`
  line
  line `(a) enter upon and inspect the metro railway or any rolling stock used thereon and its other`
  line installations;
  line
  line `(b) by order in writing addressed to the metro railway administration, require the attendance`
  line `before him of metro railway official and to require answers or returns to such inquiries as he thinks fit`
  line `to make from such metro railway official or from the metro railway administration; and`
  line
  line `(c) require the production of any book, document or material object belonging to or in the`
  line `possession or control of any metro railway administration which appears to him to be necessary to`
  line inspect.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (8361)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Commissioner to be public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8361&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner shall be deemed to be a public servant`
  line `within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (8362)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Facilities to be provided to Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8362&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The metro railway administration shall provide to`
  line `the Commissioner all reasonable facilities for the discharge of the duties or for the exercise of the powers`
  line `imposed or conferred on him by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (8363)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 34 of 2009, s. 10, for section 12 (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8363&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[The Chief Commissioner of Railway Safety shall, for each financial year,`
  line `prepare in such form, and within such time, as may be prescribed, an annual report giving a full account`
  line `of the activities of the Commissioners during the financial year immediately preceding the financial year`
  line `in which such report is prepared and forward copies thereof to the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (8364)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Annual report to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for "Commissioner" (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8364&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall cause the annual`
  line `report of the ^1[Chief Commissioner of Railway Safety] to be laid after its receipt before each House of`
  line Parliament.
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (8365)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Sanction of Central Government to the opening of metro railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "metropolitan city of Delhi" (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8365&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The metro railway in the`
  line `^1[the National Capital Region, metropolitan city and metropolitan area] shall not be opened for the public`
  line `carriage of passengers except with the previous sanction of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (8366)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Formalities to be complied with before giving sanction to the opening of metro railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8366&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `The Central Government shall, before giving its sanction to the opening of the metro railway under`
  line `section 14, obtain a report from the Commissioner that--`
  line
  line `(a) he has made a careful inspection of the metro railway and the rolling stock that may be`
  line `used thereon;`
  line
  line `(b) the moving and fixed dimensions as laid down by the Central Government have not been`
  line infringed;
  line
  line `(c) the track structure, strength of bridges, standards of signalling system, traction system,`
  line `general structural character of civil works and the size of, and maximum gross load upon, the`
  line `axles of any rolling stock, comply with the requirements laid down by the Central Government;`
  line and
  line
  line `(d) in his opinion, metro railway can be opened for the public carriage of passengers without`
  line `any danger to the public using it.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Commissioner is of the opinion that the metro railway cannot be opened without any danger`
  line `to the public using it, he shall, in his report, state the grounds therefor, as also the requirements which, in`
  line `his opinion, are to be complied with before sanction is given by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government, after considering the report of the Commissioner, may sanction the`
  line `opening of the metro railway under section 14 as such or subject to such conditions as may be considered`
  line `necessary by it for the safety of the public.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (8367)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Sections 14 and 15 to apply to the opening of certain works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8367&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of sections 14`
  line `and 15 shall apply to the opening of the following works if they form part of, or are directly connected`
  line `with, the metro railway used for the public carriage of passengers and have been constructed subsequent`
  line `to the giving of a report by the Commissioner under section 15, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) opening of additional lines of metro railway;`
  line
  line `(b) opening of stations and junctions;`
  line
  line `(c) re-modelling of yards and re-building of bridges; and`
  line
  line `(d) any alteration or reconstruction materially affecting the structural character of any work to`
  line `which the provisions of sections 14 and 15 apply or are extended by this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (8368)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Temporary suspension of traffic.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8368&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `When an accident has occurred on the metro railway`
  line `resulting in a temporary suspension of traffic, and either the original tracks and works have been restored`
  line `to their original standard or a temporary diversion has been laid for the purpose of restoring`
  line `communication, the original tracks and works so restored, or the temporary diversion, as the case may be,`
  line `may, without prior inspection by the Commissioner, be opened for the public carriage of passengers,`
  line `subject to the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the metro railway official in charge of the works undertaken by reasons of the accident has`
  line `certified in writing that the opening of the restored tracks and works, or of the temporary diversion`
  line `will not in his opinion be attended with danger to the public; and`
  line
  line `(b) a notice of the opening of the tracks and works or the diversion shall be sent immediately to`
  line `the Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (8369)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to close metro railway opened for public carriage of passengers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8369&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Where, after the`
  line `inspection of the metro railway opened and used for the public carriage of passengers or any rolling stock`
  line `used thereon, the Commissioner is of the opinion that the use of the metro railway or of any rolling stock`
  line `will be attended with danger to the public using it, the Commissioner shall send a report to the Central`
  line `Government who may thereupon direct that--`
  line
  line `(i) the metro railway be closed for the public carriage of passengers; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the use of the rolling stock be discontinued; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the metro railway or the rolling stock may be used for the public carriage of passengers`
  line `subject to such conditions as it may consider necessary for the safety of the public.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (8370)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Re-opening of closed metro railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8370&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `When the Central Government has, under section 18`
  line `directed the closure of the metro railway or the discontinuance of the use of any rolling stock--`
  line
  line `(a) the metro railway shall not be re-opened for the public carriage of passengers until it has been`
  line `inspected by the Commissioner and its re-opening is sanctioned in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `this Chapter; and`
  line
  line `(b) the rolling stock shall not be used until it has been inspected by the Commissioner and its reuse`
  line `is sanctioned in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (8371)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Use of rolling stock.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8371&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The metro railway administration may use such rolling stock as it may`
  line `consider necessary for operation and working of the metro railway:`
  line
  line `Provided that before using any rolling stock of a design or type different from that already running on`
  line `any section of the metro railway, the previous sanction of the Central Government shall be obtained for`
  line `such use:`
  line
  line `Provided further that before giving any such sanction, the Central Government shall obtain a report`
  line `from the Commissioner that he has made a careful inspection of the rolling stock and, in his opinion, such`
  line `rolling stock can be used.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (8372)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8372&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification, direct that any of its`
  line `powers or functions under this Chapter, except power to make rule under section 22, shall, in relation to`
  line `such matters and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification, be exercised or`
  line `discharged also by the Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (8373)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power to make rules in respect of matters in this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8373&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may,`
  line `by notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the duties of a metro railway administration and the Commissioner in regard to the opening of`
  line `a metro railway for the public carriage of passengers;`
  line
  line `(b) the arrangements to be made for and the formalities to be complied with before opening a`
  line `metro railway for the public carriage of passengers;`
  line
  line `(c) for regulating the mode in which, and the speed at which rolling stock used on metro railway`
  line `is to be moved or propelled; and`
  line
  line `(d) the cases in which and the extent to which the procedure provided in this Chapter may be`
  line `dispensed with.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (8374)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Exhibition of fare tables at station and supply of tickets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 34 of 2009, s. 12, for "Hindi and English" (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8374&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The metro railway`
  line `administration shall cause to be pasted in a conspicuous and accessible place at every station in ^1[Hindi,`
  line `English and official language of the State in which such station is located] a table of the fare chargeable`
  line `for traveling from the station to every place for which tickets are issued to passengers.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person desirous of travelling on the metro railway shall, upon payment of fare, be issued with`
  line `a ticket by the metro railway administration or an agent authorised in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) The ticket issued under sub-section (2) shall indicate its value, period of validity and such other`
  line `particulars as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (8375)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Exhibition and surrender of pass and ticket.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8375&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Every passenger shall, on demand by any metro`
  line `railway official authorised in this behalf, present his pass or ticket to such metro railway official for`
  line `examination at the beginning, or during or at the end of the journey and surrender such ticket,--`
  line
  line `(a) at the end of journey if the ticket is for a single journey, or`
  line
  line `(b) if such ticket is issued for a particular amount, on the exhaustion of the amount for which the`
  line `ticket was issued.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (8376)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Prohibition against travelling without pass or ticket.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8376&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `No person shall enter or remain in any`
  line `carriage on the metro railway, for the purpose of travelling therein as a passenger, unless he has with him`
  line `a proper pass or ticket.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (8377)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Carriage of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. The words "a small" omitted by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8377&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, while travelling in the metro railway, carry with him`
  line `any goods other than ^1*** baggage containing personal belongings not exceeding such volume and`
  line `weight as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person travels on the metro railway in contravention of the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1), he shall, notwithstanding that he holds a valid pass or ticket for any travel in such`
  line `railway, be liable to be removed from the train by any metro railway official authorised by the metro`
  line `railway administration in this behalf or by any other person whom such metro railway official may call to`
  line `his aid.`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (8378)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Prohibition against travelling of person suffering from infectious or contagious diseases and powers to remove them.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8378&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person suffering from infectious or contagious diseases as may be`
  line `prescribed, shall travel by the metro railway.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person travelling in contravention of any rule made under sub-section (1) shall be liable to be`
  line `removed from the metro railway.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (8379)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Communication between passengers and metro railway officials in charge of trains.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8379&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line The
  line `metro railway administration shall provide and maintain in proper order, in any metro train, such efficient`
  line `means of communication between the passengers and the metro railway official in charge of the train as`
  line `may be approved by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (8380)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Right of metro railway administration to display commercial advertisements on metro railway or on the premises occupied by it.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8380&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The metro railway administration may use its premises,`
  line `lands, buildings, posts, bridges, structures, vehicles, rolling stock and other property for displaying`
  line `commercial advertisements and for that purpose may erect or construct or fix any hoardings, billboards,`
  line `show cases, and such other things for the display of posters or other publicity materials.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (8381)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Carriage of dangerous or offensive material.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8381&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall take or cause to be taken on`
  line `the metro railway such dangerous or offensive material as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) If any metro railway official has reason to believe that any person is carrying with him, in a`
  line `container of any form, or otherwise, any dangerous or offensive material, he may cause such container to`
  line `be opened by its carrier for the purposes of ascertaining its contents.`
  line
  line `(3) Any metro railway official may remove from the metro railway any person taking with him any`
  line `dangerous or offensive material.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (8382)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to remove persons from metro railway and its carriages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8382&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Any person, entering upon`
  line `or into any part of the metro railway without lawful authority, on being asked to leave the metro railway`
  line `by any metro railway official, does not leave therefrom, may be removed from the metro railway by such`
  line `metro railway official or by any other person whom such metro railway official may call to his aid.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (8383)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8383&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules to carry`
  line `out the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for all or any`
  line `of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the particulars of the ticket such as the value, the period of validity and other particulars under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(b) the volume and weight of baggage under sub-section (1) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(c) diseases which are infectious or contagious under sub-section (1) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(d) material which is dangerous or offensive under sub-section (1) of section 30; and`
  line
  line `(e) generally, for regulating the travelling upon, and the use, working and management of the`
  line `metro railway.`
  line
  line `(3) Every metro railway administration shall keep at every station on its metro railway a copy of all`
  line `the rules made under this section and shall also allow any person to inspect it free of charge.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (8384)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Fixation of fare for carriage of passengers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8384&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The metro railway administration shall, from time`
  line `to time, on the recommendations made to it by the Fare Fixation Committee constituted under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 34, fix, for the carriage of passengers, fare for travelling from one station to`
  line `another of the metro railway:`
  line
  line `Provided that the metro railway administration may fix the fare under this section without`
  line `recommendations of the Fare Fixation Committee on the initial opening of the metro railway.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (8385)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Constitution of Fare Fixation Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1 . Subs. by Act 34 of 2009, s. 14, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8385&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, from time to`
  line `time, constitute a Fare Fixation Committee for the purpose of recommending fare for the carriage of`
  line `passengers by the metro railway.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fare Fixation Committee shall consist of a Chairperson and two other members.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as the Chairperson unless he is or has been a`
  line `Judge of a High Court.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) The Central Government and the State Government shall nominate one member each to the Fare`
  line `Fixation Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person who is or has been an Additional Secretary to the Government of India or`
  line `holds or has held an equivalent post in the Central Government or the State Government shall be qualified`
  line `to be nominated as a member.]`
  line
  line `(5) A sitting Judge of a High Court shall be appointed after consultation with the Chief Justice of that`
  line `High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (8386)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Other terms and conditions and procedure to be followed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8386&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The other terms and`
  line `conditions of the Fare Fixation Committee, and the procedure to be followed by that committee shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The metro railway administration shall provide to the Fare Fixation Committee all reasonable`
  line `facility for the discharge of its duties under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (8387)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Period for making recommendations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8387&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The Fare Fixation Committee shall submit its report`
  line `along with recommendations to the metro railway administration within such period, not exceeding three`
  line `months, as may be specified by order made by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (8388)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Recommendations to be binding on metro railway administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8388&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The recommendations`
  line `made by the Fare Fixation Committee shall be binding on the metro railway administration.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (8389)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Notice of metro railway accident.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "Government of the National Capital Territory of Delhi" (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8389&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in the course of working a metro railway,--`
  line
  line `(a) any accident attended with loss of any human life, or with grievous hurt, as defined in the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860); or`
  line
  line `(b) any collision between trains; or`
  line
  line `(c) the derailment of any train carrying passengers, or of any part of such train; or`
  line
  line `(d) any accident of a description usually attended with loss of human life or with such`
  line `grievous hurt as aforesaid; or`
  line
  line `(e) any accident of any other description which the Central Government may notify in this`
  line behalf,
  line
  line `occurs, the metro railway official in charge of the section of the metro railway on which the accident`
  line `occurs, shall, without delay, give notice of the accident in such form and containing such particulars as`
  line `may be prescribed to the Deputy Commissioner and the Deputy Commissioner of Police, within whose`
  line `jurisdiction the accident occurs, the officer in charge of the police station within the local limits of which`
  line `the accident occurs and to such other Magistrate or police officer as may be appointed in this behalf by`
  line `the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The metro railway administration, within whose jurisdiction the accident occurs, shall, without`
  line `delay, give notice of the accident to the ^1[State Government] and the Commissioner having jurisdiction`
  line `over the place of the accident.`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (8390)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Inquiry by Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8390&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the receipt of a notice under section 38 of the occurrence of`
  line `an accident resulting in loss of human life or grievous hurt causing total or partial disablement of permanent nature to a passenger, the Commissioner shall, as soon as may be, notify the metro railway`
  line `administration in whose jurisdiction the accident occurred of his intention to hold an inquiry into the`
  line `causes that led to the accident and shall at the same time fix and communicate the date, time and place of`
  line `inquiry:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall be open to the Commissioner to hold an inquiry into any other accident which,`
  line `in his opinion, requires the holding of such an inquiry.`
  line
  line `(2) If for any reason, the Commissioner is not able to hold an inquiry as soon as may be after the`
  line `occurrence of the accident, he shall notify the metro railway administration accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (8391)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Inquiry by metro railway administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8391&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Where no inquiry is held by the Commissioner`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 39 or where the Commissioner has informed the metro railway`
  line `administration under sub-section (2) of that section that he is not able to hold an inquiry, the metro`
  line `railway administration within whose jurisdiction the accident occurs, shall cause an inquiry to be made in`
  line `accordance with the prescribed procedure.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (8392)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Powers of Commissioner in relation to inquiries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8392&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of conducting an`
  line `inquiry under this Chapter into the causes of any accident, the Commissioner shall, in addition to the`
  line `powers specified in section 9, have the powers as are vested in a Civil Court while trying a suit under the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of persons and examining them on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copies thereof from any court or office; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner while conducting an inquiry under this Chapter shall be deemed to be a Civil`
  line `Court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (8393)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Statement made before Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8393&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `No statement made by a person in the course of giving`
  line `evidence in an inquiry before the Commissioner shall subject him to, or be used against him, in any civil`
  line `or criminal proceeding, except in a prosecution for giving false evidence by such person:`
  line
  line `Provided that the statement is--`
  line
  line `(a) made in reply to a question which is required by the Commissioner to answer; or`
  line
  line `(b) relevant to the subject matter of the inquiry.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (8394)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Procedure for conducting inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8394&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The metro railway administration or the Commissioner`
  line `conducting an inquiry under this Chapter may send notice of the inquiry to such persons, follow such`
  line `procedure, and prepare the report in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (8395)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `No inquiry, investigation, etc., to be made if the Commission of Inquiry is appointed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8395&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this Chapter, where a Commission of`
  line `Inquiry is appointed under the Commissions of Inquiry Act, 1952 (60 of 1952), to inquire into an`
  line `accident, any inquiry, investigation or other proceeding pending in relation to that accident shall not be`
  line `proceeded with, and all records or other documents relating to such inquiry shall be forwarded to such`
  line `authority as may be specified by the Central Government in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (8396)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Inquiry into accident not covered by section 38.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8396&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Where any accident of the nature not`
  line `specified in section 38 occurs in the course of working the metro railway, the metro railway`
  line `administration within whose jurisdiction the accident occurs, may cause such inquiry to be made into the`
  line `causes of the accident, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (8397)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title Returns.
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8397&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The metro railway administration shall send to the Central Government a return of`
  line `accidents occurring on its railway, whether attended with injury to any person or not, in such form and`
  line `manner and at such intervals as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (8398)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Power to make rules in respect of matters in this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8398&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may,`
  line `by notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the forms of notice of accidents to be given under section 38 and the particulars of the`
  line `accident such notices shall contain;`
  line
  line `(b) the persons to whom notices in respect of any inquiry under this Chapter are to be sent, the`
  line `procedure to be followed in such inquiry and the manner in which a report of such inquiry shall be`
  line prepared;
  line
  line `(c) the nature of inquiry to be made by the metro railway administration into the causes of an`
  line `accident under section 40;`
  line
  line `(d) for conducting an inquiry under clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 41;`
  line
  line `(e) the procedure of conducting inquiry and preparation of the report under section 43;`
  line
  line `(f) the making of an inquiry into the causes of the accident under section 45; and`
  line
  line `(g) the form and manner of sending a return of accidents by the metro railway administration`
  line `under section 46.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (8399)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Claims Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8399&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification, appoint a Claims`
  line `Commissioner for the purpose of adjudicating upon claims for compensation in respect of accidents`
  line `involving the death of, or bodily injury to person, or damage to any property arising out of the working of`
  line `the metro railway.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (8400)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Qualifications for appointment as Claims Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8400&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `A person shall not be qualified for`
  line `appointment as Claims Commissioner unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) is or has been, or is qualified to be, a Judge of a High Court; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been a Member of the Indian Legal Service and has held a post in Grade I of that Service;`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) has, for at least three years, held a civil judicial post carrying a scale of pay which is not less`
  line `than that of a Joint Secretary to the Government of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (8401)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Term of office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8401&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `The Claims Commissioner shall hold office as such for a term as may be`
  line `specified by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (8402)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Resignation and removal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8402&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Claims Commissioner may, by notice in writing under his`
  line `hand addressed to the Central Government, resign his office.`
  line
  line `(2) The Claims Commissioner may be removed from his office by an order of the Central`
  line `Government on the ground of proved misbehaviour or incapacity after an inquiry in which he had been`
  line `informed of the charges against him and given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in respect of those`
  line charges.
  line
  line `(3) The procedure for the investigation of misbehaviour or incapacity of the Claims Commissioner`
  line `referred to in sub-section (2) be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (8403)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Salary and allowances and other conditions of service of Claims Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8403&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `The salary`
  line `and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the Claims Commissioner`
  line `shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that neither the salary and allowances nor the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Claims Commissioner shall be varied to his disadvantage after his appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (8404)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Procedure and powers of Claims Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8404&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Claims Commissioner shall have all`
  line `the powers of a civil court for the purpose of taking evidence on oath, enforcing attendance of witnesses`
  line `and compelling the discovery or production of documents and material objects.`
  line
  line `(2) The Claims Commissioner shall be deemed to be a civil court for all the purposes of section 195`
  line `and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(3) In enquiring into and determining any claims for payment of compensation, the Claims`
  line `Commissioner may, subject to any rules that may be made in this behalf, follow such summary procedure`
  line `as he may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to any rules that may be made in this behalf, the Claims Commissioner may, for the`
  line `purpose of determining any claim for compensation, choose one or more persons possessing special`
  line `knowledge of any matter relevant to the enquiry, to assist him in holding the enquiry.`
  line
  line `(5) The Claims Commissioner shall have powers to pass such interim and final order as the`
  line `circumstance may require, including orders for payment of costs.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (8405)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Decision of Claims Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8405&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any question as to the liability of the metro railway`
  line `administration to pay compensation or as to the person to whom such compensation is payable, shall be`
  line `determined by an order of the Claims Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under sub-section (1) shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (8406)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Savings as to certain rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8406&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, where the death of, or bodily injury to, any person gives rise to a claim for`
  line `compensation under this Act and also under any other law in force, the person entitled to compensation`
  line `may claim such compensation only once either under this Act or under any other law in force.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall affect the right of any person to claim compensation payable`
  line `under any contract or scheme providing for compensation for death or personal injury or for damage to`
  line `property or any sum payable under any policy of insurance.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (8407)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8407&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules to carry`
  line `out the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(i) the procedure for investigation of misbehaviour or incapacity of the Claims Commissioner`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 51;`
  line
  line `(ii) the salary and allowances and the other terms and conditions of service of the Claims`
  line `Commissioner under section 52; and`
  line
  line `(iii) any other purpose incidental to or connected with the objects of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (8408)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Extent of liability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8408&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `The metro railway administration shall, notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in any other law, be liable to pay compensation for loss occasioned by the death of, or bodily injury to any`
  line `person to such extent as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (8409)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Application for compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8409&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `An application for compensation arising out of an accident may`
  line `be made to the Claims Commissioner by,--`
  line
  line `(a) the person who has sustained the injury or suffered any loss; or`
  line
  line `(b) all or any of the dependants of the deceased where death has resulted from the accident; or`
  line
  line `(c) an agent duly authorised by the person injured or all or any of the dependants of the deceased,`
  line `as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that where all the dependants of the deceased have not joined in any such application for`
  line `compensation, the application shall be made on behalf of or for the benefit of all the dependants of the`
  line `deceased and the dependants who have not so joined, shall be impleaded as respondents to the`
  line application.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section, the word "dependant" shall have the same`
  line `meaning as given to it in clause (b) of section 123 of the Railways Act, 1989 (24 of 1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (8410)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Drunkenness or nuisance on metro railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8410&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person, in any carriage or upon any`
  line `part of the metro railway,--`
  line
  line `(a) is in a state of intoxication; or`
  line
  line `(b) commits any nuisance or vandalism or act of indecency, or uses abusive or obscene`
  line `language; or`
  line
  line `(c) wilfully or without excuse interferes in any way with the comfort of any passenger,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees and shall also be liable to`
  line `forfeiture of the fare which he may have paid or any pass or ticket which he may have obtained or`
  line `purchased, or be removed from such carriage or part by any metro railway official authorised by the`
  line `metro railway administration in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) If any metro railway official is in a state of intoxication while on duty, he shall be punishable with`
  line `fine which may extend to two hundred and fifty rupees or, where the improper performance of the duty`
  line `would be likely to endanger the safety of any passenger travelling or being upon the metro railway, with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine which may extend to five hundred`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (8411)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Penalty for taking or causing to take offensive material upon metro railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8411&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in`
  line `contravention of sub-section (1) of section 30, a person takes or causes to be taken any offensive material`
  line `upon the metro railway, he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) In addition to the penalties specified in sub-section (1), a person takes or causes to be taken any`
  line `offensive material upon the metro railway shall be responsible also for any loss, injury or damage which`
  line `may be caused by reason of such material having been so brought upon the metro railway.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (8412)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Penalty for taking or causing to take dangerous material upon metro railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8412&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in`
  line `contravention of sub-section (1) of section 30, a person takes or causes to be taken any dangerous material`
  line `upon the metro railway, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to four`
  line `years and with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) In addition to the penalties specified in sub-section (1), a person takes or causes to be taken any`
  line `dangerous material upon the metro railway shall be responsible also for any loss, injury or damage which`
  line `may be caused by reason of such material having been so brought upon the metro railway.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (8413)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Prohibition of demonstrations upon metro railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8413&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) No demonstration of any kind`
  line `whatsoever shall be held on any part of the metro railway or other premises thereof and it shall be open to`
  line `the metro railway administration to exclude from such premises any person attending such`
  line `demonstrations whether or not he is in possession of a pass or ticket entitling him to be in the said`
  line premises.
  line
  line `(2) No person shall paste or put up any poster or write or draw anything or matter in any compartment`
  line `or carriage of the metro railway, or any premises thereof, without any lawful authority and any person`
  line `found engaged in doing any such act may be removed from the compartment, carriage or premises by any`
  line `metro railway official authorised by the metro railway administration in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever contravenes any of the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), or on being`
  line `asked by any metro railway official to leave any compartment, carriage or premises refuses to do so, shall`
  line `be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (8414)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Penalty for travelling on roof, etc., of a train.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8414&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `If any passenger travels on the roof of a train or`
  line `persists in travelling in any part of a train not intended for the use of passengers or projects any part of his`
  line `body out of a train after being warned by any metro railway official to desist, he shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to one month, or with fine which may extend to fifty rupees, or with both, and shall also be liable to be removed from the train by any metro railway official authorised`
  line `by the metro railway administration in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (8415)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Penalty for unlawfully entering or remaining upon metro railway or walking on metro track.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8415&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a person enters into or upon the metro railway without any lawful authority or having`
  line `entered with lawful authority remains there unlawfully and refuses to leave on being requested to do so by`
  line `any metro railway official, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `three months, or with fine which may extend to two hundred and fifty rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person walks on the metro track without any lawful authority, he shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to five hundred`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (8416)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Endangering the safety of passengers by metro railway official.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8416&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `If any metro railway`
  line `official, when on duty endangers the safety of any passenger,--`
  line
  line `(a) by any rash or negligent act or omission; or`
  line
  line `(b) by disobeying any rule, regulation or order which such official was bound by the terms of his`
  line `employment to obey, and of which he had notice,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to five years, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to six thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (8417)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Abandoning train, etc., without authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8417&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `If any metro railway official, when on duty, is`
  line `entrusted with any responsibility connected with the running of a train, or any other rolling stock from`
  line `one station or place to another station or place, and he abandons his duty before reaching such station or`
  line `place, without authority or without properly handing over such train or rolling stock to another authorised`
  line `metro railway official, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to four`
  line `years, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (8418)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Obstructing running of train, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8418&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `If any person obstructs or causes to be obstructed or`
  line `attempts to obstruct any train or rolling stock upon the metro railway by squatting, picketing or keeping`
  line `without authority any rolling stock on the metro railway or tampering with any signalling installations or`
  line `by interfering with the working mechanism thereof, or otherwise, he shall be liable to be removed by any`
  line `metro railway official, authorised by the metro railway administration in this behalf and shall also be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to four years, or with fine which may extend`
  line `to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (8419)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Obstructing metro railway official in his duties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8419&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `If any person wilfully obstructs or prevents`
  line `any metro railway official in the discharge of his duties, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to one year, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (8420)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Travelling without proper pass or ticket or beyond authorised distance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8420&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any`
  line passenger--
  line
  line `(a) travels in a train without having a proper pass or ticket with him; or`
  line
  line `(b) being in or having alighted from a train, fails or refuses to present for examination or to`
  line `deliver up his pass or ticket immediately on requisition being made therefor under section 24, or`
  line `travels in a train in contravention of the provisions of section 25, he shall be liable to pay, on`
  line `demand of any metro railway official appointed by the metro railway administration in this behalf,`
  line `the excess charge mentioned in sub-section (3) in addition to the ordinary single fare for the`
  line `distance which he has travelled or, where there is any doubt as to the station from which he started,`
  line `the ordinary single fare from the station from which the train originally started.`
  line
  line `(2) If any passenger travels or attempts to travel in a carriage or by a train or travels in or on a`
  line `carriage beyond the place authorised by his pass or ticket, he shall be liable to pay, on demand of any`
  line `person appointed by the metro railway administration in this behalf, the excess charge mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (3) in addition to any difference between any fare paid by him and the fare payable in respect`
  line `of the journey he has made.`
  line
  line `(3) The excess charge referred to in sub-sections (1) and (2) shall be fifty rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) If any passenger liable to pay the excess charge and fare mentioned in sub-section (1), or the`
  line `excess charge and any difference of fare mentioned in sub-section (2), fails or refuses to pay the same on`
  line `a demand being made therefor, any metro railway official authorised by the metro railway administration`
  line `in this behalf may apply to any Metropolitan Magistrate for the recovery of the sum payable as if it were a`
  line `fine, and the Magistrate if satisfied that the sum is payable shall order it to be so recovered, and may order`
  line `that the person liable for the payment shall in default of payment suffer imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to one month.`
  line
  line `(5) Any sum recovered under sub-section (4) shall, as and when it is recovered, be paid to the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (8421)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Needlessly interfering with means of communication in a train.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8421&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `If any passenger or any`
  line `other person without reasonable and sufficient cause, makes use of, or interferes with, any means`
  line `provided by the metro railway administration in a train for communication between passengers and metro`
  line `railway official in charge of the train, or misuses alarm bell of the train, he shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to one year, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or`
  line `with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (8422)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Altering or defacing or counterfeiting pass or ticket.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8422&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `If any person wilfully breaks the`
  line `security code of any pass or ticket, or defaces or alters or counterfeits or duplicates it or acts in any way to`
  line `cause revenue loss to metro railway, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (8423)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Defacing public notices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8423&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `If any person without lawful authority--`
  line
  line `(a) in this behalf pulls down or wilfully damages any board or documents set up or posted by the`
  line `order of the metro railway administration on the metro railway, or any rolling stock, or`
  line
  line `(b) obliterates or alters any letters or figures upon any such board or document or upon any`
  line `rolling stock,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to two months or with fine up to two`
  line `hundred and fifty rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (8424)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Any sale of articles on metro railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8424&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `If any person sells or exposes for sale, any article`
  line `whatsoever in any metro railway carriage or upon any part of the metro premises not authorised by metro`
  line `railway administration for such purpose, he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five`
  line `hundred rupees, and in default of payment of fine, he shall be punishable with imprisonment which may`
  line `extend to six months:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be mentioned in the`
  line `judgment of the court, such fine shall not be less than one hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (8425)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Maliciously wrecking a train causing sabotage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8425&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person--`
  line
  line `(a) loosens or displaces any rail or any other matter or thing belonging to the metro railway; or`
  line
  line `(b) turns, moves, unlocks or diverts any point or other machinery belonging to the metro railway;`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) does or causes to be done any act of sabotage in relation to the metro railway with intent or`
  line `with knowledge that it is likely to endanger safety of any person upon the metro railway,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for life, or with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to ten years:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be mentioned in the`
  line `judgment of the court, where a person is punished with rigorous imprisonment, such imprisonment shall`
  line `not be less than`
  line
  line `(i) three years in the case of a first conviction; and`
  line
  line `(ii) seven years in the case of conviction for the second or subsequent offence.`
  line
  line `(2) If a person unlawfully does any act of sabotage or any other act referred to in sub-section (1) with`
  line `intent to cause the death of any person, or with knowledge that such act is so imminently dangerous that it`
  line `must in all probability cause the death of any person or such bodily injury to any person as is likely to`
  line `cause the death of any person, he shall be punishable with death or imprisonment for life.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (8426)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Penalty for unauthorised sale of tickets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8426&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `If any person not being a metro railway official, or an`
  line `agent authorised in this behalf under sub-section (2) of section 23 sells or attempts to sell any ticket in`
  line `order to enable any other person to travel therewith, he shall be punishable for a term which may extend`
  line `to three months, or fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, or with both, and shall also forfeit the`
  line `ticket which he sells or attempts to sell.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (8427)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Maliciously hurting or attempting to hurt persons travelling by metro railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8427&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `If any`
  line `person unlawfully throws or causes to fall or strike at, against, into or upon any rolling stock forming part`
  line `of a train, any wood, stone or other matter or thing with intent, or with knowledge that it is likely to`
  line `endanger the safety of any person being in or upon such rolling stock or in or upon any other rolling stock`
  line `forming part of the same train, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for life or with imprisonment for`
  line `a term which may extend to ten years.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (8428)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Endangering safety of persons travelling by metro railway by rash or negligent act or omission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8428&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `If any person in a rash or negligent manner does any act, or omits to do what he is legally`
  line `bound to do, and the act or omission is likely to endanger the safety of any person travelling or being`
  line `upon the metro railway, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one`
  line `year, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (8429)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Damage to or destruction of certain metro railway properties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8429&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, with intent to`
  line `cause or knowing that he is likely to cause damage to or destruction of any of the properties of the metro`
  line `railway referred to in sub-section (2), causes by fire, explosive substance or otherwise causes damage to`
  line `such property, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years.`
  line
  line `(2) The properties of the metro railway referred to in sub-section (1) are the metro railway track,`
  line `tunnels, sub-way, box-structures, station buildings and installations, carriage and wagons, rolling stock,`
  line `signalling, telecommunication, air-conditioning and ventilation equipments, electrical sub-station,`
  line `drainage pump, escalators, lifts, lighting installations, ticket vending machine, ticket barriers, electric`
  line `traction and block equipments, and such other properties as the Central Government may, by notification,`
  line specify.
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (8430)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Endangering the safely of persons travelling by metro railway by wilful act or omission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8430&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line If
  line `any person by unlawful act or by any wilful omission or neglect or by tampering with safety devices,`
  line `endangers or causes to be endangered the safety of any person travelling on or being upon any metro`
  line `railway, or obstructs or causes to be obstructed or attempts to obstruct any rolling stock upon any metro`
  line `railway, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be mentioned in the`
  line `judgment of the court, such imprisonment shall not be less than--`
  line
  line `(i) six months in the case of first conviction; and`
  line
  line `(ii) two years in the case of conviction for the second or subsequent offence`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (8431)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Penalty for making a false claim for compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8431&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `If any person requiring compensation`
  line `from the metro railway administration under Chapter X makes a claim which is false or which he knows`
  line `or believes to be false or does not believe to be true, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (8432)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8432&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company, for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company,`
  line `shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of`
  line `that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (8433)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Power of arrest without warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8433&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a person commits any offence mentioned in sections`
  line `59, 61, 65 to 79, he may be arrested without warrant or other written authority by any metro railway`
  line `official or by a police officer not below the rank of a head constable or by any other person whom such`
  line `metro railway official or police officer may call to his aid:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a person has been arrested, by any person other than the police officer, he shall`
  line `be made over to a police officer, or, in the absence of a police officer, take such person or cause him to be`
  line `taken in custody to the nearest police station.`
  line
  line `(2) A person so arrested under sub-section (1) shall be produced before the nearest Magistrate, having`
  line `authority to try him or commit him for trial, as early as possible but within a period not exceeding twentyfour`
  line `hours of such arrest exclusive of the time necessary for the journey from the place of arrest to the`
  line `court of the Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (8434)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Arrest of person likely to abscond, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8434&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person commits any offence under this Act,`
  line `other than an offence mentioned in section 82 or fails or refuses to pay any excess charge or other sum`
  line `demanded under section 69 and there is reason to believe that he may abscond, or his name and address`
  line `are unknown and he refuses on demand to give his name and address, or there is reason to believe that`
  line `name and address given by him is incorrect, any metro railway official or police officer not below the`
  line `rank of head constable, or any other person whom such metro railway official may call to his aid, may,`
  line `without warrant or written authority, arrest him.`
  line
  line `(2) A person so arrested shall be produced before the nearest Magistrate, having authority to try him`
  line `or commit him for trial, as early as possible but within a period not exceeding twenty-four hours,`
  line `exclusive of the time necessary for the journey from the place of arrest to the court of the Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (8435)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Magistrate having jurisdiction under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8435&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), no court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate shall`
  line `try an offence under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (8436)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Place of trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8436&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person committing an offence under this Act, or any rule or regulation`
  line `made thereunder, shall be triable for such offence in any place in which he may be, or which the ^1[State Government] may notify in this behalf, as well as any other place in which he is liable to be tried under`
  line `any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification under sub-section (1) shall be published by the ^2[State Government] and a copy`
  line `thereof shall be exhibited for the information of the public in some conspicuous place at such metro`
  line `railway stations as that Government may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 34 of 2009, s. 16, for "Government of the National Capital Territory of Delhi" (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for "Government of the National Capital Territory of Delhi in the Delhi Gazette" (w.e.f. 7-9-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (8437)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8437&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Act, the metro railway administration in case of the non-Government metro railway`
  line `shall, in the discharge of its duties and functions under this Act, be bound by such directions on questions`
  line `of policy as the Central Government may give in writing to it from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the metro railway administration shall, as far as practicable, be given opportunity to`
  line `express its views before any direction is given under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (8438)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Prohibition to work as non-Government metro railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8438&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `No non-Government metro railway`
  line `shall work without obtaining permission from the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (8439)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8439&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government, any metro railway administration, a metro railway official or against`
  line `any other person, for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act`
  line `or any rules, regulations or orders made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (8440)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Restriction on execution against metro railway property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8440&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) No rolling stock, metro railway`
  line `tracks, machinery, plant, tools, fittings, materials or effects used or provided by a metro railway`
  line `administration for the purpose of traffic on its railway, or its stations or workshops, or offices shall be`
  line `liable to be taken in execution of any decree or order of any court or of any local authority or person`
  line `having by law the power to attach or distrain property or otherwise to cause the property to be taken in`
  line `execution, without the previous sanction of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) is to be construed as affecting the authority of any court to attach the`
  line `earnings of the metro railway administration in execution of a decree or order.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (8441)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Officials of metro railway administration to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8441&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `All persons in the`
  line `employment of the metro railway administration shall, when acting or purporting to act in pursuance of`
  line `the provisions of this Act, be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (8442)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Procedure for delivery to metro railway administration of property detained by a metro railway official.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8442&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `If a metro railway official is discharged from service or is suspended, or dies or`
  line `absconds or absents himself, and he or his spouse or widow or any member of his family or his`
  line `representative, refuses or neglects, after notice in writing for that purpose, to deliver up to the metro`
  line `railway administration or to a person appointed by the metro railway administration, in this behalf, any`
  line `station, dwelling house, office or other building with its appurtenances, or any books, papers, keys,`
  line `equipments or other matters, belonging to the metro railway administration and in the possession or`
  line `custody of such metro railway official on the occurrence of any such event as aforesaid, any Metropolitan`
  line `Magistrate may, on application made by or on behalf of the metro railway administration, order any`
  line `police officer, with proper assistance, to enter upon the station, office or other building and remove any`
  line `person found therein and take possession thereof, or to take possession of the books, papers and other`
  line `matters, and to deliver the same to the metro railway administration or to a person appointed by the metro`
  line `railway administration in that behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (8443)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Proof of entries in records and documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8443&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `(1) Entries made in the records or other`
  line `documents of the metro railway administration shall be admitted in evidence in all proceedings by or`
  line `against the metro railway administration, and all such entries may be proved either by the production of`
  line `the records or other documents of the metro railway administration containing such entries or by the`
  line `production of a copy of the entries certified by the officer having custody of the records or other`
  line `documents under his signature and stating that it is a true copy of the original entries and that such`
  line `original entries are contained in the records or other documents of the metro railway administration in his`
  line possession.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, a court shall presume that the entries in the`
  line `records of the metro railway administration admitted in evidence under sub-section (1) are true, unless`
  line `there is evidence to the contrary.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (8444)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Service of notice, etc., on metro railway administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8444&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `Any notice or other document`
  line `required or authorised by this Act to be served on a metro railway administration may be served--`
  line
  line `(a) by leaving it at the office of the metro railway administration; or`
  line
  line `(b) by registered post to the office address of the metro railway administration.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (8445)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Service of notice, etc., by metro railway administration`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=8445&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `Any notice or other document`
  line `required or authorised by this Act to be served on any person by the metro railway administration may be`
  line `served by--`
  line
  line `(a) delivering it to the person; or`
  line
  line `(b) leaving it at the usual or the last known place of abode of the person; or`
  line
  line `(c) registered post addressed to the person at his usual or the last known place of abode.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (28595)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Presumption where notice is`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=28595&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `Where a notice or other document is`
  line `served by registered post, it shall be deemed to have been served at the time when the letter containing it`
  line `would be delivered in the ordinary course of post, and in proving such service, it shall be sufficient to`
  line `prove that the letter containing the notice or other document was properly addressed and registered.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (28596)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Representation of metro railway administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=28596&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) The metro railway administration may,`
  line `by order in writing, authorise any of its official or other person to act for, or represent it, as the case may`
  line `be, in any proceeding before any civil, criminal or other court.`
  line
  line `(2) A person authorised under sub-section (1) to conduct prosecution on its behalf shall,`
  line `notwithstanding anything in section 302 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), be entitled`
  line `to conduct such prosecutions without the permission of the Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (28597)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Appointment of security staff.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=28597&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `The metro railway administration may constitute and maintain`
  line `security staff for its railway, and the powers, duties and functions of such staff shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (28598)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=28598&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, direct that all or any`
  line `of the powers under this Act or rules made thereunder, except sections 22, 32, 47, 56, 99 and 100,`
  line `exercisable by it, shall, in relation to such matters and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be`
  line `specified in the notification, be exercisable also by such officer or authority subordinate to the Central`
  line `Government or by such officer of the metro railway administration.`
  line
  line `(2) The metro railway administration may, by general or special order in writing, delegate to any of`
  line `its official subject to such conditions and limitations, if any, as may be specified in the order, such of its`
  line `powers and functions under this Act, except its power under section 101.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (28599)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Power to remove difficulties`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=28599&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (28600)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=28600&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the form and time for preparing and sending annual report under section 12;`
  line
  line `(b) the terms and conditions of the Fare Fixation Committee under section 35;`
  line
  line `(c) the procedure to be followed by the Fare Fixation Committee under section 35;`
  line
  line `(d) the extent of compensation payable under section 57;`
  line
  line `(e) the powers, duties and functions of the security staff of the Government metro railway under`
  line `section 97; and`
  line
  line `(f) without prejudice to any power to make rules contained elsewhere in this Act, generally to`
  line `carry out the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (28601)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Power of metro railway administration to make regulations`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=28601&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `The Government metro`
  line `railway administration may, with the previous approval of the Central Government, make regulations not`
  line `inconsistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder, to provide for all matters for which provisions`
  line `are necessary or expedient for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (28602)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=28602&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made by the Central`
  line `Government and every regulation made by a Government metro railway administration under this Act`
  line `shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session,`
  line `for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive`
  line `sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive`
  line `sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or both Houses`
  line `agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or`
  line regulation.
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (28603)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Effect of Act inconsistent with other enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=28603&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have`
  line `effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any enactment other than this Act or`
  line `in any instrument having effect by virtue of any enactment other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (28604)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Application of other Acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=28604&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the provisions of this Act`
  line `shall be in addition to and not in derogation of the Metro Railways (Construction of Works) Act, 1978 (33`
  line `of 1978).`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (28605)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698&sectionId=28605&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00020_200260_1517807324698
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Delhi Metro Railway (Operation and Maintenance) Ordinance,`
  line `2002 (Ord. 7 of 2002) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance, shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
